Bruce L. Claflin: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 3:57 AM ET
Healthcare Equipment and Supplies

Company Overview of IDEXX Laboratories, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Bruce L. Claflin  Independent Director, IDEXX Laboratories, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships66$250,542
Background

		Mr. Bruce L. Claflin served as the Chief Executive Officer of 3com Corporation at Tippingpoint Technologies Inc. from January 2001 to January 2006. Mr. Claflin served as the President and Chief Operating Officer at 3com Corp., from August 1998 to January 2001. He served as the President of 3Com Corporation's Business Network Company since December 2002. He served as Vice President and General Manager of DEC's Personal Computer Business Unit from October 1995 to June ... 1997. He served as Senior Vice President and General Manager of Worldwide Sales and Marketing of Digital Equipment Corp. and also served as its Executive Vice President of Sales and Marketing from July 1997 to June 1998. He joined Digital Equipment Corp. in November 1995. He held Senior management and executive positions at International Business Machines Corporation  from April 1973 to October 1995. He served as an Assistant Group Executive and General Manager responsible for IBM's Asia and South Pacific operations since 1989 and served as the President of IBM Personal Computer Company - Americas from August 1993 to June 1994. Mr. Claflin served as General Manager of Product and Brand Management for the IBM Personal Computer Company from June 1994 to October 1995. He served as General Manager, Mobile Computing for IBM Personal Computer Company from June 1992 to August 1993 where he was responsible for introducing IBM's ThinkPad line of mobile computers. He served as the Chairman of Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. from March 2, 2009 to May 12, 2016. He served as Chairman of H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. He has been an Independent Director of IDEXX Laboratories, Inc. since July 14, 2015 and CIENA Corp. since August 31, 2006. He served as an Independent Director of Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. since August 12, 2003 until April 26, 2017. He served as a Director of H3C Technologies Co., Limited. While at IBM, Mr. Claflin served as a Director on the boards of several IBM International subsidiaries as well as the IBM Credit Corporation and TSS, a joint venture between IBM and Kodak. He served as a Director of 3Com Corporation from 2001 to January 2006. He served as a Director of TW telecom inc. from August 1999 to December 1, 2003. In 1998, Pennsylvania State University named him an Alumni Fellow, in recognition of his professional achievements and support of the University. In June 2002, he was again honored by Pennsylvania State with the Distinguished Alumnus Award for his personal, professional and community service achievements. In 2003, he was named a Distinguished Alumnus of Penn State, its highest honor for lifetime achievements. Mr. Claflin holds a Bachelor of Arts in Political Science from Pennsylvania State University in 1973.Read Full Background




